These Terms of Use ("Terms") govern your access to and use of the AuroraNow mobile application ("App"). By downloading or using the App, you agree to be bound by these Terms.

1. Use of the App

AuroraNow provides space weather data, aurora forecasts, and local viewing conditions. You agree to use the App only for lawful purposes and in a way that does not infringe the rights of, restrict, or inhibit anyone else's use of the App.

2. Disclaimers and Limitation of Liability

a. Unpredictability of Nature
The Aurora Borealis / Australis is a natural phenomenon. While AuroraNow uses real-time solar wind data and advanced algorithms to provide accurate forecasts, we do not guarantee that you will see the aurora. Space weather changes rapidly, and local weather (clouds, light pollution) heavily impacts visibility.

b. Assumption of Risk
Aurora hunting often involves traveling at night, sometimes to remote or dark locations, and in cold weather. You are solely responsible for your own safety, travel decisions, and well-being. AuroraNow and its developer shall not be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages, injuries, or expenses incurred while using the App or attempting to view the aurora based on our alerts.

